YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>greeting: "Hello World!"
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
  "greeting": "Hello World!"
}
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
  &lt;greeting&gt;Hello World!&lt;/greeting&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>: <pre><code>greeting = "Hello World!"
</code></pre></p> <p>Python Usage: <pre><code>from doti18n import LocaleData

i18n = LocaleData("locales")

# Access as raw string
print(i18n["en"].greeting)   # Output: Hello World!
</code></pre></p>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>:</p> <pre><code># key-value
hello: "Hello World!"

# list
fruits:
    - "Apple"
    - "Banana"
    - "Orange"

# nested list
items:
    - name: "Item 1" 
    - name: "Item 2"

# nested dict
errors:
    connection: "Connection error occurred."
    timeout: "Request timed out."

# pluralization
notifications:
    one: "You have {count} new notification."
    other: "You have {count} new notifications."
</code></pre> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    // key-value
    "hello": "Hello World!",

    // list
    "fruits": [
        "Apple",
        "Banana",
        "Orange"
    ],        

    // nested list
    "items": [
        {"name": "Item 1"},
        {"name": "Item 2"}
    ],

    // nested dict
    "errors": {
        "connection": "Connection error occurred.",
        "timeout": "Request timed out."
    },

    // pluralization
    "notifications": {
        "one": "You have {count} new notification.",
        "other": "You have {count} new notifications."
    }
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Note</p> <p>Standard JSON does not support comments. The comments above are for illustration only.</p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;!-- key-value --&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Hello World!&lt;/hello&gt;

    &lt;!-- list --&gt;
    &lt;fruits list="true"&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Apple&lt;/fruit&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Banana&lt;/fruit&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Orange&lt;/fruit&gt;
    &lt;/fruits&gt;

    &lt;!-- nested list --&gt;
    &lt;items list="true"&gt;
        &lt;item&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Item 1&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;/item&gt;
        &lt;item&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Item 2&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;/item&gt;
    &lt;/items&gt;

    &lt;!-- nested dict --&gt;
    &lt;errors&gt;
        &lt;connection&gt;Connection error occurred.&lt;/connection&gt;
        &lt;timeout&gt;Request timed out.&lt;/timeout&gt;
    &lt;/errors&gt;

    &lt;!-- pluralization --&gt;
    &lt;notifications&gt;
        &lt;one&gt;You have {count} new notification.&lt;/one&gt;
        &lt;other&gt;You have {count} new notifications.&lt;/other&gt;
    &lt;/notifications&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>:</p> <pre><code># key-value
hello = "Hello World!"

# list
fruits = [
    "Apple",
    "Banana",
    "Orange"
]

# nested list
[[items]]
name = "Item 1"
[[items]]
name = "Item 2"

# nested dict
[errors]
connection = "Connection error occurred."
timeout = "Request timed out."

# pluralization
[notifications]
one = "You have {count} new notification."
other = "You have {count} new notifications."
</code></pre>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <pre><code>cats: "{count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}"
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "cats": "{count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}"
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
  &lt;cats&gt;{count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}&lt;/cats&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre> <pre><code>cats = "{count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}"
</code></pre> <p>Python Usage: <pre><code>i18n["en"].cats(count=5)  # Output: 5 cats
</code></pre></p>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <pre><code>status: "{gender, select, male {He} female {She} other {They}}"
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "status": "{gender, select, male {He} female {She} other {They}}"
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
  &lt;status&gt;{gender, select, male {He} female {She} other {They}}&lt;/status&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre> <pre><code>status = "{gender, select, male {He} female {She} other {They}}"
</code></pre> <p>Python Usage: <pre><code>i18n["en"].status(gender="female")  # Output: She
</code></pre></p>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <pre><code>rank: "{pos, selectordinal, one {#st} two {#nd} few {#rd} other {#th}}"
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
  "rank": "{pos, selectordinal, one {#st} two {#nd} few {#rd} other {#th}}"
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
  &lt;rank&gt;{pos, selectordinal, one {#st} two {#nd} few {#rd} other {#th}}&lt;/rank&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre> <pre><code>rank = "{pos, selectordinal, one {#st} two {#nd} few {#rd} other {#th}}"
</code></pre> <p>Python Usage: <pre><code>i18n["en"].rank(pos=3)  # Output: 3rd
</code></pre></p> <p>Forcing / Disabling ICUMF</p> <ul> <li>Force: Prepend <code>icu:</code> to a string in your file (e.g., <code>"icu:My {custom} format"</code>).</li> <li>Disable: Pass <code>Loader(icumf=False)</code> when initializing <code>LocaleData</code>.</li> </ul>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>hello: "Hello World!"
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.yaml</code>: <pre><code>hello: "Bonjour le monde!"
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{"hello": "Hello World!"}
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.json</code>: <pre><code>{"hello": "Bonjour le monde!"}
</code></pre></p> <p>Note</p> <p>The root element is ignored in XML files. See Supported Formats for details.</p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Hello World!&lt;/hello&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Bonjour le monde!&lt;/hello&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>: <pre><code>hello = "Hello World!"
</code></pre> <code>locales/fr.toml</code>: <pre><code>hello = "Bonjour le monde!"
</code></pre></p>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>cat: "I have {count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}"
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    "cat": "I have {count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}"
}
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;cat&gt;I have {count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}&lt;/cat&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>: <pre><code>cat = "I have {count, plural, one {# cat} other {# cats}}"
</code></pre></p> <p>Usage:</p> <pre><code>from doti18n import LocaleData

i18n = LocaleData("locales")

print(i18n["en"].cat(count=1))   # Output: I have 1 cat
print(i18n["en"].cat(count=3))   # Output: I have 3 cats
print(i18n["en"].cat(count=11))  # Output: I have 11 cats
</code></pre>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>__macros__:
  brand: "doti18n"
  author: "darkj3suss"

welcome: "Welcome to @brand!"
credits: "Created by @author."
nested:
  info: "More about @brand."
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    "__macros__": {
        "brand": "doti18n",
        "author": "darkj3suss"
    },
    "welcome": "Welcome to @brand!",
    "credits": "Created by @author.",
    "nested": {
        "info": "More about @brand."
    }
}
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;__macros__&gt;
        &lt;brand&gt;doti18n&lt;/brand&gt;
        &lt;author&gt;darkj3suss&lt;/author&gt;
    &lt;/__macros__&gt;
    &lt;welcome&gt;Welcome to @brand!&lt;/welcome&gt;
    &lt;credits&gt;Created by @author.&lt;/credits&gt;
    &lt;nested&gt;
        &lt;info&gt;More about @brand.&lt;/info&gt;
    &lt;/nested&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>: <pre><code>[__macros__]
brand = "doti18n"
author = "darkj3suss"

welcome = "Welcome to @brand!"
credits = "Created by @author."

[nested]
info = "More about @brand."
</code></pre></p> <p>Python Code:</p> <pre><code>from doti18n import LocaleData

i18n = LocaleData("locales")

print(i18n["en"].welcome)      # Output: Welcome to doti18n!
print(i18n["en"].credits)      # Output: Created by darkj3suss.
print(i18n["en"].nested.info)  # Output: More about doti18n.
</code></pre> <p>Performance</p> <p>Since macro replacement happens only once during the loading phase, it has zero performance overhead when you access your translations during runtime.</p>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>: <pre><code>cat:
    one: "{count} cat"
    other: "{count} cats"
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    "cat": {
        "one": "{count} cat",
        "other": "{count} cats"
    }
}
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;cat&gt;
        &lt;one&gt;{count} cat&lt;/one&gt;
        &lt;other&gt;{count} cats&lt;/other&gt;
    &lt;/cat&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>: <pre><code>[cat]
one = "{count} cat"
other = "{count} cats"
</code></pre></p> <p>Usage:</p> <pre><code>from doti18n import LocaleData

i18n = LocaleData("locales")

print(i18n["en"].cat(1))   # Output: 1 cat
print(i18n["en"].cat(3))   # Output: 3 cats
print(i18n["en"].cat(11))  # Output: 11 cats
</code></pre>

YAMLJSONXMLTOML <p><code>locales/en.yaml</code>:</p> <pre><code># key-value
hello: "Hello World!"

# list
fruits:
    - "Apple"
    - "Banana"
    - "Orange"

# nested list
items:
    - name: "Item 1" 
    - name: "Item 2"

# nested dict
errors:
    connection: "Connection error occurred."
    timeout: "Request timed out."

# pluralization
notifications:
    one: "You have {count} new notification."
    other: "You have {count} new notifications."
</code></pre> <p>Note</p> <p>Standard YAML features (anchors, aliases, complex structures) are fully supported.</p> <p><code>locales/en.json</code>: <pre><code>{
    // key-value
    "hello": "Hello World!",

    // list
    "fruits": [
        "Apple",
        "Banana",
        "Orange"
    ],        

    // nested list
    "items": [
        {"name": "Item 1"},
        {"name": "Item 2"}
    ],

    // nested dict
    "errors": {
        "connection": "Connection error occurred.",
        "timeout": "Request timed out."
    },

    // pluralization
    "notifications": {
        "one": "You have {count} new notification.",
        "other": "You have {count} new notifications."
    }
}
</code></pre></p> <p>Note</p> <p>Standard JSON does not support comments. The comments above are for illustration only.</p> <p><code>locales/en.xml</code>: <pre><code>&lt;locale&gt;
    &lt;!-- key-value --&gt;
    &lt;hello&gt;Hello World!&lt;/hello&gt;

    &lt;!-- list --&gt;
    &lt;fruits list="true"&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Apple&lt;/fruit&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Banana&lt;/fruit&gt;
        &lt;fruit&gt;Orange&lt;/fruit&gt;
    &lt;/fruits&gt;

    &lt;!-- nested list --&gt;
    &lt;items list="true"&gt;
        &lt;item&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Item 1&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;/item&gt;
        &lt;item&gt;
            &lt;name&gt;Item 2&lt;/name&gt;
        &lt;/item&gt;
    &lt;/items&gt;

    &lt;!-- nested dict --&gt;
    &lt;errors&gt;
        &lt;connection&gt;Connection error occurred.&lt;/connection&gt;
        &lt;timeout&gt;Request timed out.&lt;/timeout&gt;
    &lt;/errors&gt;

    &lt;!-- pluralization --&gt;
    &lt;notifications&gt;
        &lt;one&gt;You have {count} new notification.&lt;/one&gt;
        &lt;other&gt;You have {count} new notifications.&lt;/other&gt;
    &lt;/notifications&gt;
&lt;/locale&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>XML Parsing Logic</p> <ul> <li>Root Element: Ignored. You can name it anything (e.g., <code>&lt;locale&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;data&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;xml&gt;</code>), it serves only as a container.</li> <li>Lists: Tags with identical child names are automatically treated as lists.</li> <li>Explicit Lists: To force a list (e.g., for a single element), add the <code>list="true"</code> attribute to the parent tag. Using <code>list="true"</code> explicitly is recommended for consistency.</li> </ul> <p><code>locales/en.toml</code>:</p> <pre><code># key-value
hello = "Hello World!"

# list
fruits = [
    "Apple",
    "Banana",
    "Orange"
]

# nested list
[[items]]
name = "Item 1"
[[items]]
name = "Item 2"

# nested dict
[errors]
connection = "Connection error occurred."
timeout = "Request timed out."

# pluralization
[notifications]
one = "You have {count} new notification."
other = "You have {count} new notifications."
</code></pre> <p>Note</p> <p>Standard TOML features (arrays of tables, inline tables, multi-line strings) are fully supported.</p>
